BMW Wants to Raise Sales of Front-Wheel Drive Cars, Auto Says

-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 
2011-06-02T09:28:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/bmw-wants-to-raise-sales-of-front-wheel-drive-cars-auto-says.html
Bayerische Motoren Werke AG (BMW)  plans to
increase the percentage of front-wheel drive cars it sells,
 Auto-Motor-und-Sport  reported, citing unidentified people at the
company.  The carmaker plans to raise the share to more than 40
percent of sales,  Auto-Motor-und-Sport  said.  BMW wants to sell 2.6 million cars annually until 2020,
with 1.09 million of them front-wheel drive cars, Auto-Motor-
und-Sport said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julie Cruz in Frankfurt at 
 jcruz6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at   arummer@bloomberg.net  